Check Batch Data Transform Status

After you’ve created at least one batch data transform, clicking the Data Transforms tab leads you to the Recently Viewed screen, where you can view a data transform's status.

DATA TRANSFORM STATUS	DESCRIPTION


Active

	The data transform is active and available to run.


Processing

	The data transform is in progress.


Deleting

	The data transform is in the process of being removed.


Error

	The data transform encountered an error and isn’t active.
LAST RUN	DESCRIPTION


None

	The batch data transform hasn't run.


Pending

	The batch data transform is preparing to run, either based on the schedule set by the user or by the user having clicked Run Now.


In Progress

	The batch data transform is running.


Success

	The batch data transform ran successfully on all nodes.


Failure

	The batch data transform couldn’t run.


Canceled

	The user canceled the batch data transform.

If the job fails or completes with a warning, click the job name to get more details.

View an individual batch data transform’s status by clicking on its name. The Details screen shows the last run status, the data transform status, its definition, created date, and time of its last run.

The Refresh History tab on the Details screen shows the status for each time the batch data transform has run. You can view error messages about a data transform, the date it was last run, and the status of its last run.
